  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="title">System Architecture</div>

      <div class="intro">
        Empyrria is not a collection of symbols.  
        It is a structured system where each element has a defined role.
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Core of Being</h2>
        <p>
          The Core defines identity.  
          It does not change. It cannot be replaced.
        </p>
        <p>
          It determines resonance, direction, and the fundamental reason an entity acts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Doctrine</h2>
        <p>
          Doctrine defines structure and truth.  
          It exists independently of individuals.
        </p>
        <p>
          It acts as a stabilizing layer that gives meaning direction and limits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>State</h2>
        <p>
          A state is an alignment condition.  
          It is trainable, temporary, and dependent on discipline.
        </p>
        <p>
          It determines how power is applied, not what that power is.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Discipline</h2>
        <p>
          Discipline defines execution.  
          It is the learned method through which actions are performed.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Phenomenon</h2>
        <p>
          Phenomena are system events.  
          They are not chosen, but experienced.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Sigil</h2>
        <p>
          A sigil is the symbolic layer.  
          It represents and stabilizes elements of the system.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Command / War</h2>
        <p>
          Command aligns multiple entities under a shared intent.
        </p>
        <p>
          It transforms individual alignment into collective action.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        The system only works when these layers remain aligned.  
        Power without alignment leads to collapse.  
        Alignment allows power to remain stable.
      </div>

